      section#projects.resume-section.projects-section
        .resume-section-content
          h2.mb-5 Projects
          p.mb-4
            | A few of the things I’ve been building recently. Most of these started as course projects or side projects and grew into experiments in UX, performance, and real-world usefulness.
          .row.g-4
            // SLC Trips
            .col-md-6
              .card.h-100.shadow-sm
                .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
                  h5.card-title.mb-3
                    i.fas.fa-route.me-2
                    | SLC Trips
                  p.card-text
                    | A trip-planning site focused on Salt Lake City that helps visitors quickly discover routes, hikes, neighborhoods, and places to explore. 
                    |  I’ve been using it as a sandbox to learn about performance, SEO, and building a clear, simple UX for travel planning.
                  .mt-auto
                    .mb-3
                      span.badge.bg-primary.me-2 TypeScript
                      span.badge.bg-secondary.me-2 React
                      span.badge.bg-success.me-2.me-2 Node.js
                      span.badge.bg-info.me-2 Travel
                    .d-flex.gap-2
                      a.btn.btn-outline-primary.btn-sm(href='https://github.com/ShreeshSrivastava', target='_blank' rel='noopener')
                        i.fab.fa-github.me-1
                        | GitHub
                      a.btn.btn-primary.btn-sm(href='#!' target='_blank')
                        i.fas.fa-external-link-alt.me-1
                        | Live Site

            // Dishbook
            .col-md-6
              .card.h-100.shadow-sm
                .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
                  h5.card-title.mb-3
                    i.fas.fa-utensils.me-2
                    | Dishbook
                  p.card-text
                    | A recipe web app where users can save, search, and organize dishes in a clean, distraction-free interface. 
                    |  Built as a full-stack project to practice RESTful design, authentication, and templating.
                  .mt-auto
                    .mb-3
                      span.badge.bg-primary.me-2 Python
                      span.badge.bg-secondary.me-2 Django
                      span.badge.bg-success.me-2 PostgreSQL
                    .d-flex.gap-2
                      a.btn.btn-outline-primary.btn-sm(href='https://github.com/ShreeshSrivastava', target='_blank' rel='noopener')
                        i.fab.fa-github.me-1
                        | GitHub
                      a.btn.btn-primary.btn-sm(href='#!' target='_blank')
                        i.fas.fa-external-link-alt.me-1
                        | Live Demo

            // Multiplayer Snake (Blazor)
            .col-md-6
              .card.h-100.shadow-sm
                .card-body.d-flex.flex-column
                  h5.card-title.mb-3
                    i.fas.fa-gamepad.me-2
                    | Real-Time Multiplayer Snake
                  p.card-text
                    | A real-time multiplayer Snake game using an authoritative C# server and a Blazor client. 
                    |  The project uses a custom TCP protocol, JSON messages, and a canvas-based frontend to explore networking, concurrency, and game-loop design.
                  .mt-auto
                    .mb-3
                      span.badge.bg-primary.me-2 C#
                      span.badge.bg-secondary.me-2 Blazor
                      span.badge.bg-success.me-2 TCP
                      span.badge.bg-info.me-2 Canvas
                    .d-flex.gap-2
                      a.btn.btn-outline-primary.btn-sm(href='https://github.com/ShreeshSrivastava', target='_blank' rel='noopener')
                        i.fab.fa-github.me-1
                        | GitHub
                      a.btn.btn-primary.btn-sm(href='#!' target='_blank')
                        i.fas.fa-file-alt.me-1
                        | Write-up

            // (Add more project cards here as needed)

      hr.m-0

